Class SubmissionManager

java.lang.Object
com.hado90.submissionMgt.SubmissionManager
public class SubmissionManager extends Object
Manages a collection of submissions, providing functionality to add, retrieve, and filter submissions by their status. The class also includes an internal iterator for traversing submissions based on a specific status.

    • addSubmission

      public void addSubmission(String submissionPath)
      Adds a submission to the collection, ensuring no duplicate submission IDs. If the submission ID does not already exist, the submission is added.
      Parameters:
      submissionPath - the path of the submission to be added

    • bulkAddSubmissions

      public void bulkAddSubmissions(List<String> submissionPaths)
      Adds multiple submissions to the collection. Each submission is added only if it doesn't already exist in the collection.
      Parameters:
      submissionPaths - a list of submission paths to be added

    • getAllSubmissions

    • filterSubmissionsByStatus

      public Map<String,Submission> filterSubmissionsByStatus(String status)
      Filters submissions based on their status. Returns a map of submission IDs and their corresponding submission objects that match the given status.
      Parameters:
      status - the status to filter submissions by (e.g., "SUBMITTED", "INVALID")
      Returns:
      a map of submission IDs and submission objects matching the given status
